In [17]:
df_filtered = df[(df['Year'] >= 2000) & (df['Year'] <= 2014)]

medals_by_country = df_filtered.groupby('Country')['Medal'].count().reset_index()

medals_by_country_sorted = medals_by_country.sort_values(by='Medal', ascending=True)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 20))
plt.barh(medals_by_country_sorted['Country'], medals_by_country_sorted['Medal'], color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Number of Medals')
plt.ylabel('Country')
plt.title('Number of Medals by Each Country for the Summer Olympic Games(2000-2014)')
plt.show()

gdp_ranking = df3[['Country', 'GDP per Capita']].dropna().sort_values(by='GDP per Capita', ascending=False)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 30))
plt.barh(gdp_ranking['Country'], gdp_ranking['GDP per Capita'], color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('GDP per Capita')
plt.ylabel('Countries')
plt.title('Ranking each Country by GDP per Capita')
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()  
plt.show()
